public class PersistenceWorkerFactoryImpl
extends Object

Implementation of PersistenceWorkerFactory. This implementation searches to find the appropriate implementation type of PersistenceWorker for each PersistentObject type in a mappings file.

Constructor Detail

PersistenceWorkerFactoryImpl

public PersistenceWorkerFactoryImpl(Properties properties)
Creates a new PersistenceWorkerFactory object. The factory is initialized with the type associations that are retrieved by a mappings file. The mappings file contains a list of file paths to mapping properties file. Each mapping properties file associates PersistentObject types with the corresponding implementation type of PersistenceWorker.

Parameters:
properties - Properties file that contains the property pwMappingsFile which shows to the path of the file that contains the list of mappings files.

initialize

protected void initialize(String mappingsFilePath)
                   throws IOException
Initializes the Factory with the type associations that are retrieved from a mappings file. The mappings file contains a list of paths to properties files that can be found inside the local classpath. Each properties file contains associations between a declaration type and an implementation type. Declaration type is usually an interface and implementation type is the concrete class that implements it.
Implementation type can also be a concrete class. In this case, the corresponding implementation class has to be the same class, or a subclass of the declaration class.
Different properties files can provide different mapping for the same type. In this case, the last mapping will overwrite any other. This implies that the order in which the properties files are placed in the mappings files catalog, is important.

Parameters:
mappingsFilePath - Path to the file that contains the paths to the mapping files.
Throws:
IOException
